# Experimental Environment

# LLM Configuration

The LLM conditions used the following API and model configuration:

| Parameter | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Provider | Groq API |
| Model | llama-3.3-70b-versatile |
| API Type | Remote inference API |
| Prompting Type | Structured behavioral prompting |
| Output Type | JSON-formatted reasoning and decision output |

The same LLM model was used across all LLM conditions to isolate the effect of prompt structure rather than differences in model capability.

---

# Experimental Conditions

Four experimental conditions were tested.

## 1. baseline

This condition included only rule-based agents.

Agent behavior was determined using predefined heuristic strategies such as:

- cooperative behavior,
- defecting behavior,
- random contribution,
- tit-for-tat-like adaptation,
- and conditional cooperation.

Purpose:

To establish a non-cognitive baseline for comparison.

---

## 2. belief_mixed

This condition introduced belief-based agents.

These agents estimated future contributions of other agents based on historical observations and simple belief updating

---

## 3. llm_notom_mixed

This condition included LLM agents without explicit Theory-of-Mind prompting.

The LLM agents received game history and contextual information but were not instructed to reason explicitly about beliefs, intentions, or mental states of other agents.

---

## 4. llm_tom_mixed

This condition included LLM agents with explicit Theory-of-Mind prompting.

These agents were instructed to:

- infer likely motivations of other agents,
- estimate future behavior,
- reason about cooperation patterns,
- and predict future contributions before selecting their own contribution.
